<HEADLINE>
<P>
RECORD RACK: IN BRIEF:; 
</P>
<P>
*** EN VOGUE, "BORN TO SING," ATLANTIC.: ALBUMS ARE RATED FROM FIVE STARS (A 
CLASSIC) TO ONE STAR (POOR). 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS HUNT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Unlike most female groups, these four R&amp;B singers can really sing -- and do 
some passable rapping too. 
</P>
<P>
Best known for the hit single "Hold on," En Vogue, on its debut album, 
admirably performs a batch of mostly well-crafted ballads and medium-tempo 
songs. Grating, dissonant vocal blends do spoil a few otherwise strong songs. 
The ingeniously arranged "Time Goes On" is the class of this collection. DENNIS 
HUNT 
</P>
</TEXT>
