<HEADLINE>
<P>
STONING CLAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
You want us to believe that he's a sweet, sensitive guy and that the Diceman is 
just an act. So I can't help but wonder -- what if the baby he's expecting is 
born with physical or mental handicaps? Will the Diceman still think those 
jokes are funny? What if that child chooses a homosexual lifestyle or selects a 
mate of another race and gives him "urine-colored" grandchildren. 
</P>
<P>
Will the Diceman still be laughing? 
</P>
<P>
As the mother of a handicapped child, I am far too aware of the ignorance and 
bigotry that is focused on those who are born into a life of challenge. His act 
merely encourages this ignorance to fester and grow to it's enormous, ugly 
potential. For every joke he tells, a thousand mothers have cried themselves to 
sleep in pain for the way their children are treated. And if handing one 
unfortunate individual $1,000 is all it takes to clear his conscience, then he 
never really had one. 
</P>
<P>
CATHERINE BACOS CLINCH 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
