<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE MATURE TRAVELER: EAST EUROPE OFFERED BY INTERHOSTEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL HUGHES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Trips to Czechoslovakia and Hungary plus another that takes in East and West 
Germany and both Berlins are three of six new destinations offered by 
Interhostel this fall. 
</P>
<P>
Other new fall international study/travel trips for mature travelers, age 50 
and over, include Melbourne and Adelaide, Australia (Sept. 30-Oct. 14), Bangkok 
and Phuket, Thailand (Oct. 22-Nov. 6), and Mexico City and Cuernavaca, Mexico 
(Oct. 27-Nov. 9). 
</P>
<P>
All of these popular trips, plus eight others, should be booked as early as 
possible. 
</P>
<P>
All Interhostel trips combine lectures and seminars with social programs and 
excursions to historic and modern points of interest. Local entertainment 
performances and opportunities to meet with residents are also part of each 
program. 
</P>
<P>
Trips average between two and three weeks and $1,195 and $1,595. That includes 
accommodations, frequently in host-country universities or local hotels, meals, 
the study programs, plus all field trips, activities as well as ground travel 
within the country. 
</P>
<P>
Air fare is not included, but can be arranged through Interhostel on group-rate 
flights. 
</P>
<P>
The Czechoslovakia trip (Sept. 30-Oct. 14) is set mostly in Prague with side 
trips to Pilsen, the spas of Karlsbad and Marienbad as well as other 
countryside attractions. It runs $1,545. 
</P>
<P>
Budapest is the center of the Hungary trip, (Oct. 1-15) with side tours to 
Puszta, Eger and a four-day stay in Rackeve Castle, once the property of Prince 
Eugene of Savoy. Cost is $1,475. 
</P>
<P>
The Germany trip includes a three-day stay in Hamburg, both East and West 
Berlin, with a side tour to Potsdam, then down to Leipzig where lecturers from 
Karl Marx University will discuss contemporary European topics. Set for Nov. 
5-19, it runs $1,595. 
</P>
<P>
Interhostel, now in its 10th year, and sponsored by the Continuing Education 
Department of the University of New Hampshire, also has its popular previously 
offered programs. These are: 
</P>
<P>
Salzburg, Austria (Sept. 11-25), $1,595; London, England (Sept. 16-30, $1,395; 
Leningrad/Kiev/Moscow (Sept. 16-30), $1,394; Beijing/Shanghai/Xian/Hangzhou, 
China (Sept. 16-30), $1,395; Nairobi, Kenya (Oct. 8-24), $1,495; San Jose, 
Costa Rica (Nov. 1-14, $1,145; Christchurch, New Zealand (Jan. 22-Feb. 6), 
$1,895; and Christmas in Vavaria (Dec. 3-17), $1,295. 
</P>
<P>
For more information and a free catalogue of all trips, write Interhostel, 
University of New Hampshire, 6 Garrison Ave., Durham, N. H. 03824-3529. Or 
phone (800) 733-9753 Monday through Friday from 1 to 4:30 p.m. Eastern time. 
</P>
<P>
Grand Circle Travel, a major national tour company for senior travel and a 
leader in European long-stay apartment or hotel vacations, is offering free 
single supplements for its extended-stay vacations in Spain and Portugal during 
November and December. 
</P>
<P>
This means a savings of $45 to $80 per week, depending on the choice of 
accommodations offered. And the company's records show the average stay is 
about three weeks. 
</P>
<P>
Single seniors can spend a full week on Spain's Costa del Sol for as little as 
$975 including hotel or apartment accommodations, transfers and round-trip air 
fare from Los Angeles on regularly scheduled carriers. Additional weeks may be 
added for only $97 each. 
</P>
<P>
The Extended Vacation choices in Spain include: Torremolinos, Benalmedena and 
Nerja. In Portugal, Grand Circle has accommodation in Cascais, the Algarve and 
Madeira. 
</P>
<P>
For a Portugal November or December, no single supplement visit, prices begin 
at $1,275 from Los Angeles, including air fare, apartment or hotel 
accommodations, daily breakfast and transfers. 
</P>
<P>
For more information, write Grand Circle Travel, 347 Congress St., Boston, 
Mass. 02210. Or call (800) 248-3737. (Call between 8 a.m. to 7 p.m. Monday 
through Friday, or 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. on Saturday, Eastern time. 
</P>
<P>
Mature travelers in the Lakewood area might want to check out Blake Travel and 
its Good Times Travel Club for seniors. 
</P>
<P>
The full-service travel agency operates a wide range of day trips by motor 
coach, extended two- to seven-day tours of California and nearby states as well 
as longer domestic and international tours and cruises. 
</P>
<P>
One of the trips coming up to northern California includes two train rides: the 
Napa Valley Wine Train and the Skunk train out of Fort Bragg. The Aug. 13 to 20 
trip also includes visits to Eureka, Mendocino, Sacramento and Salinas, with 
dinner at the Steinbeck House. Price is $719 per person, double. 
</P>
<P>
Blake's Good Times Travel Club is free. A 24-page newsletter is $1 ($5 for 
about eight issues a year). For more information: Good Times Travel Club, Blake 
Travel, 5683 Woodruff Ave., Lakewood, Calif. 90713. Phone (213) 920-2653. 
</P>
<P>
The venerable older Atherton Hotel in San Francisco is offering a "Time of Your 
Life" special rate for mature travelers for $39 a night, single or double, from 
Sunday through Thursday night stays, through December. 
</P>
<P>
Long popular with seniors and European visitors, the Atherton is located at 685 
Ellis St. on the fringe of the Bay City's Tenderloin district. 
</P>
<P>
It provides a friendly, European-style welcome, has a restaurant for breakfast 
and lunch. Phone (800) 227-3608 and ask for the "Time of Your Life" $39 rate. 
</P>
<P>
Also in San Francisco, the more upscale Hotel Bedford has a $50 rate, single or 
double, for mature travelers on Sunday through Tuesday nights now through July. 
Regular rates start at $94 single. The Bedford is at 761 Post St. near Union 
Square. Phone (800) 652-1889. 
</P>
</TEXT>
