<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA FE VIEWPOINT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
My daughter and I just returned last week from a trip to Santa Fe, which (made 
me) interested me in your June 3 article on that town by Jerry Hulse. 
</P>
<P>
I would agree with your restaurant recommendations, with the exception of the 
Coyote Cafe. We had been looking forward to a return visit to this trendy 
restaurant since our first visit in 1987. What a disappointment! We suggest an 
alternative just a block away: the restaurant in the Hotel St. Francis. You'll 
find real Santa Fe hospitality there in addition to Old World charm. 
</P>
<P>
SONJA ROBINSON 
