<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOME VICTORY! 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Deputy Atty. Gen. Charles Getz, who argued the state's case in the El Cajon 
malathion spraying trial, is reported to have said the court's decision was "a 
victory for the environment, period." ("El Cajon Gets Its Second Dose of 
Malathion," June 5.) 
</P>
<P>
Orwellian Doublespeak of the first order! 
</P>
<P>
I was struck by the similarity of his attitude to that of an American officer 
present at Ben Tre, Vietnam, in February, 1968, who is reported to have said, 
"It became necessary to destroy the town in order to save it." 
</P>
<P>
If the governor and his minions continue their chosen course, they will not 
only degrade our shared environment in known and unforeseen ways, they will 
also erode the public trust in our government, demonstrate the arrogance of 
unaccountable bureaucrats and seriously impact the public health. For what? The 
shelf life of an avocado in an export market? 
