<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE PLOTS THICKEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I was shocked to learn that the "Buena Park Community" is the only one of its 
kind in Orange County (June 5). 
</P>
<P>
Since February, my daughter and I have weeded, dug, planted and harvested two 
plots in the "Community Organic Garden" at Golden West College in Huntington 
Beach. 
</P>
<P>
The peas, broccoli, red and green cabbage, strawberries, lettuce, cucumbers, 
zucchini, onions, carrots, etc., are now so abundant that we are able to not 
only enjoy a very healthy and tasty diet ourselves but also share our harvests 
with our neighbors and friends. 
</P>
<P>
More experienced gardeners have been wonderful about sharing their "tips" on 
composting, mulching, gopher control, etc. In addition to our individual plots, 
we have community areas with fruit trees, herbs, flowers and berries. 
</P>
<P>
I am extremely grateful to Golden West College for providing the opportunity to 
the community to participate in this ecologically sound as well as healthy 
activity. 
</P>
<P>
DAWN C. DARINGTON 
</P>
<P>
Westminster 
</P>
