<HEADLINE>
<P>
GYMNAST LEONARD WINS VAULT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Angie Leonard of Sepulveda finished first in the junior division vault in the 
United States Assn. of Independent Gymnastic Clubs meet in Greensboro, N.C., 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
But Leonard could not hold the lead in the all-around competition. Leonard, who 
had been suffering from the flu during the meet, held the lead in both the 
all-around and vaulting events after the preliminaries 
</P>
</TEXT>
