tournaments, umpires are sometimes called upon to decide measurement 
disagreements. Here, distance of two bowls to white jack ball is measured. ; 
Photo, Lionel Stein takes intent look at his target. ; Photo, Joe Beagin, age 
81, keeps one foot on mat, as required by lawn bowling rules. ; Photo, Robert 
Marsh, president of the San Diego Lawn Bowling Club, rolls a bowl at Balboa 
Park. DON BARTLETTI / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
