<HEADLINE>
<P>
GENDER FACTOR IN NOVEMBER GOVERNOR'S RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As a long-time Democrat, I want to express appreciation to Pete Wilson for 
opening up the fall gubernatorial campaign on a positive note. 
</P>
<P>
His new television ad shows how, as senator, he worked constructively with 
then-Mayor Feinstein to solve problems in San Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
Although it is reported that Wilson starts out with a substantial funding 
advantage, it is gratifying that he would open the campaign by using some of it 
to highlight Feinstein's skill in working with opposition legislators to 
achieve goals, and her graciousness ("You're wonderful!") in dealing with 
friend and foe alike. 
</P>
<P>
As governor she will be able to work with state legislators of both parties 
and, starting in 1991, Gov. Feinstein's good rapport with Sen. Wilson will 
benefit all Californians. 
</P>
<P>
MARK ADAMS 
</P>
<P>
Sherman Oaks 
