<P>
NATIONWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
POLL FINDS 68% BACK FLAG AMENDMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
More than two-thirds of Americans favor amending the U.S. Constitution to 
outlaw flag desecration, according to a Gallup Poll conducted for Newsweek 
magazine. 
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the survey reflected a growing understanding of the Supreme 
Court's finding that flag-burning is a protected form of free speech. Although 
68% said they wanted the amendment, the poll also found 37% in agreement with 
the court, compared to 28% who backed a similar ruling issued a year ago. In 
addition, 73% said that a candidate's position on flag-burning was important to 
them in an election for governor, Congress or a state legislature. 
</P>
