<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOOD COVERAGE TO SPARE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I would just like to thank ESPN for its fine coverage of the Masters Bowling 
Tournament on May 19. 
</P>
<P>
ESPN allowed the bowlers to finish out their games while we watched rather than 
going to commercials, and the last game was played without commercial 
interruption. It was so different from watching ABC, which is continually going 
to commercials while the competitors bowl through their frames, and then 
apprises viewers of the scores afterward. I don't know of any other sports 
where that sort of thing is allowed to happen. If it did, the fans would be 
irate, but even now in bowling it is allowed to continue this way. 
</P>
<P>
Toni Jacobson, Monterey Park 
</P>
</TEXT>
